# Deployment — {{ project_name }}

Phase 3 of the lifecycle: **Discovery → Delivery → Deployment**. This is the
runbook the team executes when a delivered, eval-passing build goes to real
users. It is written once at G2 (delivery → deployment) and revised per release.

Phase and gate state live in `LIFECYCLE.md` (machine-readable, written by
`/gate-check`). This file is the **human** operating document: rollout stages,
rollback criteria, the A/B decision procedure, and the alert checklist. Keep it
current — a stale runbook is worse than none.

> **Gate G2 must be green before deployment.** Run `/deploy-check` — it audits
> G2 readiness (eval-gate, security review, sanyi audit, deployment-target
> decision, this runbook) and reports what's missing. It does **not** write
> `LIFECYCLE.md` — only `/gate-check` does; `/deploy-check` is the launch-day
> pre-flight, `/gate-check` is the recorded verdict.

