## G2 readiness — what "ready to deploy" means

Deployment does not begin until every G2 check passes (per the lifecycle
schema in `LIFECYCLE.md`):

| G2 check | Evidence |
|---|---|
| `eval_gate_green` | `{{ eval_root }}/targets.yaml` has ≥1 **activated** (uncommented) target — a fully-commented file passes `make eval-gate` vacuously (CI/CD only WARNs on it so canary iteration isn't blocked; readiness holds the real line). Then `make eval-gate` passes against those targets, including the margin-over-naive-baseline row. |
| `security_review_clean` | `/security-review` run for the shipping commit, no unresolved findings. |
| `sanyi_audit_clean` | `/sanyi audit` passes — no cross-layer contract violations in what's shipping. |
| `deployment_target_resolved` | DESIGN.md's deployment decision is `Resolved` (this project: `{{ deployment_target }}`), not Open/Deferred. |
| `runbook_monitoring_documented` | This file's Rollout, Rollback, and Monitoring sections are filled — not placeholders. |

