## Rollout stages (canary)

Ship in stages; each stage has an explicit **promote** and **rollback**
trigger. Do not advance on a timer alone — advance on the metrics below holding.

| Stage | Traffic | Promote when | Rollback when |
|---|---|---|---|
| **0 — Shadow** | 0% (mirror, no user-visible response) | Errors/latency comparable to prod; eval metrics on shadow traffic within target | Any hard error class the golden set didn't cover |
| **1 — Canary** | ~5% | Health checks green + no regression on the guardrail metrics below for the bake window | Guardrail metric breaches its floor, or error rate rises vs. control |
| **2 — Ramp** | 25% → 50% | Canary metrics hold at each step; A/B (below) shows no significant harm | Any guardrail regression that a bootstrap CI (ml) confirms is real, not noise |
| **3 — Full** | 100% | 50% stable for the bake window; on-call sign-off | — (rollback path is redeploy of the previous image) |

**Bake window:** <!-- set per release, e.g. 24h or N thousand interactions -->

**Guardrail metrics** (the ones that trigger rollback — a subset of the eval
suite chosen because a regression here is user-visible harm):
{%- if include_metric_escalation %}
- Escalation rate — must not rise vs. control.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_metric_friction %}
- Friction score — must not rise vs. control.
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_metric_intent %}
- Intent-resolution rate — must not fall vs. control.
{%- endif %}
- Error rate / p95 latency — must stay within the prod envelope.
<!-- Name the specific floor/ceiling for each. A guardrail without a number
     can't trigger a rollback. -->

### How the canary is deployed
{%- if deployment_target in ['docker', 'cloud'] %}
`.github/workflows/cd.yml` builds and pushes the image (tagged `sha` + `latest`)
to GHCR and — for a `docker`/`cloud` target — carries a **canary** job that
gates the `latest` promotion behind a manual `workflow_dispatch` approval after
the sha-tagged image bakes.
{%- if has_corpus_pipeline or include_interaction_evals %}
The `build-canary` job runs the **eval gate first** (`--gate`, before the docker
build): a threshold miss in `{{ eval_root }}/targets.yaml` aborts the canary. With
no target activated yet it prints a loud WARNING and proceeds (`--warn-empty`) —
so a fresh scaffold isn't blocked, but `/deploy-check`'s G2 still refuses to call
it launch-ready until ≥1 target is real.
{%- endif %} Your platform (Railway/ECS/Cloud Run/…) points its
canary revision at the sha tag and the stable revision at `latest`; promotion =
re-pointing `latest`. See the comments in `cd.yml`.
{%- else %}
This project's `deployment_target` is `{{ deployment_target }}` — no `cd.yml`
build/canary job ships (serverless/local deploy via the platform's own git
integration). Implement the staged rollout with your platform's traffic-split
primitive (Vercel/Lambda alias weights, etc.) following the stage table above.
{%- endif %}

