## Rollback

Rollback is **redeploy of the last-known-good image/revision** — never a
forward-fix under pressure. Criteria (any one triggers it):

1. A guardrail metric breaches its floor and an ml bootstrap CI (see the A/B
   bridge below) confirms the difference is real, not sampling noise.
2. Error rate or p95 latency exceeds the prod envelope for longer than one
   health-check interval.
3. A `/security-review` finding surfaces post-deploy at the shipping commit.

<!-- Record the last-known-good tag/revision here at each promotion so rollback
     is one command, not an investigation. -->

