## A/B evaluation (ml ↔ evals bridge)

Canary and ramp decisions are **statistical**, not eyeballed. The bridge
between the eval suite (which scores interaction quality) and the ml stats
toolkit (which decides whether a score difference is real) is documented in
{% if include_ml %}[`ml/AB_BRIDGE.md`](ml/AB_BRIDGE.md){% else %}the ml A/B bridge doc — add the `ml` capability (`/add-capability ml`) to ship `ml/AB_BRIDGE.md` and the `ml/stats_testing` toolkit it documents{% endif %}.

The short version: eval metrics on control vs. canary traffic → ml
`stats_testing` (`required_sample_size` before you start, `mann_whitney_test`
+ `bootstrap_cliffs_delta` after) → promote only when the effect is
non-negative with a CI that excludes meaningful harm.

