## Monitoring & alerts

A launch is not done when traffic hits 100% — it's done when someone is
watching it. Fill and keep current:

- [ ] **Health checks** — every service exposes `/health`; the platform (or an
      external uptime check) polls it and pages on failure. Endpoints:
      <!-- list each service's /health URL -->
- [ ] **Structured logs** — shipping to <!-- destination -->; error-rate alert
      threshold set.
{%- if include_ml or include_metric_escalation or include_metric_friction or include_metric_intent %}
- [ ] **Eval logging** — interaction samples logged for offline re-grading
      (W&B / the eval report pipeline) so guardrail regressions are caught in
      the next grading run, not just live.
{%- endif %}
- [ ] **On-call / operator** — who is paged, and by what.
      <!-- DESIGN.md's operator-model row names this. -->
- [ ] **Rollback rehearsed** — the redeploy-previous path has been run at least
      once in staging.

